    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter" xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">Frans van Cranevelt to Miklós Oláh ([Ghent], 10 September
                    1536)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">He is sending the epitaph he has written on Erasmus of
                            Rotterdam’s death. Here it is rumored that Damme has capitulated and the
                            King has been captured. </p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb facs="https://www.eleveltar.hu/kereso-portlet/spring/digitalcontent/getcontent/preservica/BA132218-D9FE-4405-999E-2216A527681E
                    "/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Franciscus Craneveldius, <app xml:id="app.1">
                        <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.1"><add corresp="Olahus" type="insert"
                                >caesaris Caroli a consiliis,</add></lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II #III" xml:id="rdg.1">caesaris Caroli a consiliis</rdg>
                    </app> Nicolao Olao salutem.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">Mitto tibi, Vir Eruditissime quale, quale epitaphium viri
                    incomparabilis <persName>Erasmi Roterodami</persName>,<note xml:id="note.1"
                        >Erasmus died on 12 July, 1536.</note> quod inter Belgicas Eumenides nobis
                    expressit amor viri, quamquam sentio Musas inter arma veluti puellas verecundas
                    iampridem conticescere, sed hoc ipsum tua <app xml:id="app.2">
                        <lem wit="#CE #I #III" xml:id="lem.2">linea</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II" xml:id="rdg.2"><del corresp="Olahus">lana</del><add
                                corresp="Olahus" type="corr">linea</add></rdg>
                    </app>, cum per se sit, incultum splendorem poterit accipere. Quae hic <app
                        xml:id="app.3">
                        <lem wit="#CE #I #III" xml:id="lem.3">vulgariter</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II" xml:id="rdg.3"><del corresp="Olahus">vulgariter</del><add
                                corresp="Olahus" type="corr">vulgata</add></rdg>
                    </app> sunt de <app xml:id="app.4">
                        <lem wit="#CE #I" xml:id="lem.4"><del corresp="Olahus">deditura</del><add
                                corresp="Olahus" type="corr">deditione</add></lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II #III" xml:id="rdg.4">deditione</rdg>
                    </app><app xml:id="app.5">
                        <lem wit="#CE #I #III" xml:id="lem.5">Dammi</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#II" xml:id="rdg.5"><del corresp="Olahus">damni</del><add
                                corresp="Olahus" type="corr">Dammi</add></rdg>
                    </app><note xml:id="note.2">Damme.</note> ac regis captivitate, multi facile
                    credunt. Utinam respublica Christiana hisce bellis quam minima Christiani
                    sanguinis iactura defungatur. Recte vale, Domine Colendissime. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.3">Ex nostro musaeo<note xml:id="note.3">It is probably in Ghent, see
                        Ep. 241.<ref>olahus.tei.15320722_1</ref></note> X. mensis Septembris 1536. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.4"
                    ><?oxy_custom_start type="oxy_content_highlight" color="255,255,0"?>[Epitaphium
                    Erasmi Roterodami]<?oxy_custom_end?><note xml:id="note.4"><hi rend="smallcap"
                            >Ipolyi</hi> 1875, 581, in Romanian: <hi rend="smallcap"
                            >Capoianu–Costa–Nicolae</hi> 2022,
                    1230–1231.</note><?oxy_custom_start type="oxy_content_highlight" color="255,255,0"?></p>
                <p xml:id="p.5">[Aliud]<?oxy_custom_end?><note xml:id="note.5"><hi rend="smallcap"
                            >Ipolyi</hi> 1875, 581, in Romanian: <hi rend="smallcap"
                            >Capoianu–Costa–Nicolae</hi> 2022, 1230–1233.</note></p>
